wwwroot is a root directory by convention for all static web files
if you start asp .net core application from blank page, creating normal directory
and naming it "wwwroot" will change the icon to a one in the current form. 

We can use static resources within our controllers and views without 
any additional code if we configure our project properly 

For more info on wwwroot visit 
https://www.tutorialsteacher.com/core/aspnet-core-wwwroot
or 
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-gb/aspnet/core/fundamentals/static-files?view=aspnetcore-3.1